        <div class="Rulesmo">
            <div class="headerngrules">
                <h5> We ask for your understanding and compliance with the specified Rules and Regulations during our Tours. You may follow the advice of the assigned tour guide for each group, listen to safety protocols, and avoid negligence to prevent any accidents or disruptions to your vacation. Keep safe, everyone!</h5>
                    <img src="ATV BACKGROUND/Rules and Regulation.png">
            </div>
          
            
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <b>Safety Gear</b><p> All riders are required to wear appropriate safety gear, including helmets, gloves, and goggles, throughout the entire duration of the ATV ride.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                   <b> Age Limit</b> <p>Only individuals of legal age and possessing a valid driver's license or those under the supervision of a legal guardian are allowed to operate the ATV.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <b> No Alcohol or Drugs</b><p> Riding under the influence of alcohol or drugs is strictly prohibited. Any rider suspected of being impaired will not be allowed to participate.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <b>Follow the Guide</b><p> Riders must follow the designated ATV guide at all times during the tour. Instructions given by the guide must be followed promptly.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                     <b>Stay on Designated Trails</b><p> It is prohibited to venture off the designated ATV trails to protect the local flora and fauna and ensure the safety of the riders.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                     <b>One Rider per ATV</b> <p>Each ATV is designed for a single rider. Riding with a passenger is not allowed, except in ATVs specifically designed for two persons.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <b>Maintain Safe Distance</b> <p>Riders must maintain a safe distance from the ATV ahead of them to avoid collisions.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <b> No Racing or Stunts</b> <p>Racing, reckless driving, or performing stunts with the ATVs is strictly prohibited.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <b> Environmental Responsibility</b><p> All riders must respect the environment and not leave any trash or litter during the tour.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <b> Assumption of Risk</b> <p>Riders must sign a liability waiver and assume responsibility for any risks associated with ATV riding before participating in the activity.</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>

